<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dumathoin</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hear my story, and tale of horror, dear friends! <P>The second time that I had ever cruised on the ship from Faydwer to Freeport, this is what happened... <P>Ship makes brief stopover at an Island (Sisters Island?). A fellow passenger, an obviously stupid warrior-type with very low intelligence, jumps off ship at the Island, he then finds a RED very deadly NPC (near the docks) to pick a fight with and then trains that deadly NPC back onto the ship. <P>The rampaging RED NPC jumps into the ship. Ship starts moving. No player can ever cast spells on board a ship. Deadly RED NPC kills 2 low-level passengers on board the moving ship. He also kills the apparently stupid warrior passenger that trained him in the first place. Deadly NPC nearly kills my Paladin... my life was spared because the ship zoned from Ocean of Tears into Freeport which then immediately removes the NPC. <P>Is this a glitch in the game? <P>Why is this even allowed to happen???? <P>One stupid action by a player ends up nearly wiping out the entire passenger crew of a moving ship. It is a known thing that ships are not meant for fighting. You cannot cast spells inside ship, so you can barely defend yourself inside ship. <P>I reported him to the GM on duty. <BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Venomblood</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I've had something similar happen with a character of mine on the Sister's Island. I jumped ship to grab Kiola nuts and then ran back to the ship to catch it before it left. If you're fast, you can do this easily. However, there is a pirate that spawns near the hut where the nuts are sold, and if he's close enough, he may aggro. He's green to my character, but he aggro'd anyway. I ran to the ship figuring he'd lay off once aboard, I never attacked him once, but he followed. So I attacked him so I could kill him before he did any damage to the other passengers. Have you ever tried fighting on the boat? Some of the worst pathing in the game. You can have the guy standing right in front of you and you won't be able to hit him. When he finally got low on hp's, I chased him all over the place, including below decks, all the while getting messages that he's too far away to hit, and I'm right next to him! Then, go cap it off, the boat zones to BB, and the game boots me. Back to Sister's Isle. I didn't know NPC's would follow you onto the ship, or I never would have dragged it there. Hope this helps everyone to avoid similar mistakes.<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Pulex</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Happened to me once at low lvl....headed to Butcherblock and as we stopped at Sister Isle, cyclops jumps on board..well everyone bailed off to strand themselves in zone, 3 others die...I ran blindly downstairs and hid behind the bar until we zoned....gotta be careful out there<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Oakao</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Last night while praticing sneak to pass time on long boat ride form Freeport to Butcher Block: Splash, Ahhhhh I fell of the boat. Can I hop back on the boat somehow as it passes. Or do I have to swim all the way to a dock?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Soporific</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I was in Freeport, waiting for a ride when some high lev guy gave me Dead Man Walking or something like that.  I could walk on the water, etc.  Well I went over to one of the sides of FP, and really aggro'd some NPC, who came over immediately and started chasing me everywhere.  I finally stopped running on the dock and started to fight, getting my ass kicked down to about 1 bubble, when the boat arrived.  I charged down the dock and hopped on the boat, and the NPC didn't get on.  This was only a week or two ago, so maybe they have changed the rules/code.  <P>Good Luck.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">taobob</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Actually NPC's will only chase you onto the boat in OOT if I remember correctly... <P>All other zones where an NPC is chasing you, getting on the boat will cause them to cease pursuit (but not change aggro status).<P>I think that this was instituted to discourage people from using the boats as a way to escape a hopeless situtation, especially in the OOT zone where higher level NPCs are...<P>------------------<BR>Blackivar Backbiter<BR>aka Blackivar the Cunning<BR>Halfling Rogue<BR>21st Season<BR>Druzzil Ro Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Uvasno</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">This hapened to me about 2 weeks ago.  I didn't really mind that I got wasted. The part that bothered me was 1)waiting for the boat again and 2)finding my body somewhere in the water.<P>Uvasno<BR>Bruins Marauders<BR>Ranger on Luclin</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dolomite</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Early on in the game.. way way back within the first few months.. I was crossing from Erudin to Queynos via boat.  This HUGE and I mean REALLY HUGE shark the size of the boat pops up on the deck randomly.. jaw chomping.  Unfortunately a noob (we were all noobs back then) was between his teeth.. crunch, crunch, dead.  He didn't live too long.  It scared the heck out of me, and I figured I was next.. luckly the shark just sat on the deck of the boat for a while and then popped off to never never land.  I zoned and was luckily spared.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Treebringer Coyoteuglly</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dying in OOT on the boat from a clops is a know bug and a GM should give you a FULL exp rez.<P>If you fall of a boat and are to lazy to swim you can play chicken with the boat to get back on.  Just swim into it head on while looking up and it should pop you back up.  Also a know :bug:<P>------------------<BR>Do not meddle in the affirs of Dragons for you are crunchy and taste like chicken.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
